  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConfigurationLoaderInterface, ConfigurationLoader<T>, Version, Serializable

    public class OA4MPConfigurationLoader<T extends ServiceEnvironmentImpl>
extends AbstractConfigurationLoader<T>
    This made to be over-ridden and extended with new features, hence the separate call for creating the service environment. All of the elements are protected rather than private.

    Usage

    • Extend this, adding in new extensions to the XML configuration
    • Choose a servlet (such as Init) which has to be loaded first, using Tomcat's load-on-startup parameter
    • Set an instance of this as the Bootstrapper by over-riding MyProxyDelegationServlet loadEnvironment and setting the instance directly. This side-steps Tomcat's loading issues and Java single inheritance limitations at once
